# Artifactory JSON Builder — Project Standards

**Mod reference:** https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/artifactory

This project is a React SPA for generating JSON data files consumed by the Artifactory Minecraft mod. All JSON output must match the mod's codec schemas exactly.

## Mod Reference Docs

The `existing_markdown/` folder contains markdown exports of the CurseForge mod pages. These are the authoritative source of truth for mod behavior, configuration fields, and feature descriptions. Always consult these files when working on mod-related content or UI copy.

| File                               | Mod         |
| ---------------------------------- | ----------- |
| `existing_markdown/artifactory.md` | Artifactory |
| `existing_markdown/homebound.md`   | Homebound   |

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev       # Start dev server with HMR
npm run build     # Type-check + production build (tsc -b && vite build)
npm run lint      # ESLint
npm run preview   # Preview production build
```

No test suite is configured.

## Stack

- Vite 8 + React 19 + TypeScript 5 (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4 via `@tailwindcss/postcss`
- `react-hook-form` + `zod` for form state and validation
- `react-router-dom` v7 for client-side routing
- No additional runtime dependencies without discussion

## Architecture

The app is an "Attunement Data Source Config Generator" that produces Artifactory mod configuration JSON. It is a multi-page SPA with the following routes under a shared `Layout`:

| Route                       | Page                                      |
| --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `/`                         | `Home` — mod card grid                    |
| `/artifactory`              | `Artifactory` — tabbed mod reference page |
| `/artifactory/json-builder` | `JsonBuilder` — form wrapper              |

### Data flow

1. `App.tsx` sets up routing and renders `Layout` with an `<Outlet />`
2. `JsonBuilderForm` (`src/features/jsonBuilder/`) owns all form state via `react-hook-form` with a Zod resolver
3. Nested attunement levels are managed as field arrays; each level is rendered by `AttunementLevelItem`
4. `output.ts` serializes form state to clean JSON (omits empty/nullish fields) and handles clipboard copy and file download
5. `JsonPreview` renders syntax-highlighted live JSON output

### Key files

| File                                               | Role                                                                                                                              |
| -------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `src/features/jsonBuilder/fieldConfig.ts`          | Zod schemas and default values — source of truth for the data model                                                               |
| `src/features/jsonBuilder/JsonBuilderForm.tsx`     | Main form orchestration, validation, layout                                                                                       |
| `src/features/jsonBuilder/AttunementLevelItem.tsx` | Collapsible per-level editor (nested field arrays)                                                                                |
| `src/features/jsonBuilder/output.ts`               | JSON transformation, clipboard/download utilities, path helpers                                                                   |
| `src/components/`                                  | Shared UI primitives: `Button`, `FormField`, `StringListInput`, `JsonPreview`, `Tooltip`, `SectionHeader`, `Breadcrumb`, `Layout` |
| `src/components/inputStyles.ts`                    | Shared Tailwind class strings for inputs/selects                                                                                  |
| `src/pages/Artifactory.tsx`                        | Tabbed mod reference page (Overview, Getting Started, Configuration, FAQ)                                                         |
| `src/hooks/useTheme.ts`                            | Persists light/dark mode to `localStorage`                                                                                        |
| `src/utils/cn.ts`                                  | Minimal `cn()` class-merging utility                                                                                              |

**When changing the data model**, update `fieldConfig.ts` first (schema + defaults), then propagate to the form and output serializer.

## Writing Standards

- Do not use em dashes (—) in UI copy or documentation. Use commas, semicolons, colons, or parentheses instead.

## Code Standards

**TypeScript**

- All types must be derived from Zod schemas via `z.infer<>` — never manually duplicate them
- Use `type` imports for type-only imports (`import type { Foo }`)
- Avoid `any`; use `never` casts only at react-hook-form generic boundaries

**React**

- Functional components only, named exports
- Keep components small and single-purpose; extract to `src/components/` if reused across features
- Use `useFieldArray` from react-hook-form for all dynamic list fields
- Clean up `setTimeout` refs in `useEffect` return to prevent state updates after unmount

**Tailwind**

- Use Tailwind utility classes directly — no custom CSS unless unavoidable
- Always include `focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2` on interactive elements for keyboard accessibility

**JSON Output**

- All output goes through `toCleanOutput()` in `output.ts` — never serialize raw form values
- Omit any field that is empty string, empty array, or unset boolean (`''`)
- Number fields are stored as strings internally and parsed in `toCleanOutput`

## File Structure

```
src/
  components/       # Shared UI primitives (Button, FormField, StringListInput, etc.)
  features/
    jsonBuilder/    # All codec-specific form logic and output
  hooks/            # App-level hooks (useTheme)
  pages/            # Route-level page components (Home, Artifactory, JsonBuilder)
  utils/            # Utility functions (cn)
```

## Asset Organization

All static images live in `public/` and are organized by mod. Never place mod-specific assets in the `public/` root.

```
public/
  <mod-slug>/           # One folder per mod (e.g. artifactory/, homebound/)
    title.png           # The mod's title/wordmark image (used in landing card + page header)
    logo.png            # Square icon logo, if one exists
    <screen-name>.png   # Screenshots, UI images, etc. named descriptively
    items/              # Cropped individual item sprites
      <item-name>.png
```

- Use kebab-case for all filenames (e.g. `nexus-ui.png`, `homeward-bone.png`)
- The title image is always named `title.png` and the logo (if separate) is always `logo.png`
- Reference assets as absolute public paths: `/artifactory/banner.png`, `/homebound/items/homeward-bone.png`
- Never use external CDN URLs (forgecdn, flickr, etc.) in source code; download and commit all images
